@pcottle Oops, can't believe I forgot to link it when creating the issue. [Here](https://github.com/jbnicolai/tmux-fpp) it is!

When running fpp normally in tmux it works exactly as expected. However, you have to remember to insert `fpp` in the pipeline when executing your command. What this plugin allows is for the user to press a key combination (`prefix + i`) and run fpp over the most recently created `stdout` and `stderr` in the active TTY.

If you look at this gif in the original issue you see `fpp` is never executed manually on `git diff`. The user ran `git diff`, realized he wanted to pick a path and pressed `prefix + i` afterwards.

